The failure of the rear leaf spring shackle can cause the leaf spring to pierce through the truck bed, leading to damage and potentially causing loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Loud bang or noise from the rear of the vehicle
raised area or hole in the truck bed
broken or damaged leaf spring shackle
and excessive pressure on the shock absorber.
